00071 void ALGraph::AddDEdge(unsigned source, unsigned destination, unsigned weight)
00072 {
00073   // create adjacency info element for this edge
00074   AdjacencyInfo adjInfo = { destination, weight };
00075   // and create iterate in order to insert into the vector
00076   std::vector<AdjacencyInfo>::iterator it;
00077 
00078   for (it = alist[source - 1].begin(); it < alist[source - 1].end(); ++it)
00079   {
00080     // if the weight is less than the weight of the current node in alist
00081     if (weight < it->weight)
00082     {
00083       // then insert it here and return
00084       alist[source - 1].insert(it, adjInfo);
00085       return;
00086     }
00087     // if the weight is equal, sort by id
00088     if (weight == it->weight)
00089     {
00090       if (destination < it->id)
00091       {
00092         alist[source - 1].insert(it, adjInfo);
00093         return;
00094       }
00095     }
00096   }
00097   // if a spot cannot be found to insert the edge before other edges in the 
00098   // adjacency list, then just push it to the back of the list.
00099   alist[source - 1].push_back(adjInfo);
00100 }

00115 void ALGraph::AddUEdge(unsigned node1, unsigned node2, unsigned weight)
00116 {
00117   // in order to make the edge undirected, add two directed edges
00118   // one in each direction
00119   AddDEdge(node1, node2, weight);
00120   AddDEdge(node2, node1, weight);

00160 std::vector<DijkstraInfo> ALGraph::Dijkstra(unsigned start_node) const
00161 {
00162   // the return vector of least cost paths to each node from the start_node
00163   std::vector<DijkstraInfo> dInfo;
00164 
00165   // override the default behavior of priority_queue to allow the use of pop
00166   // to get the node from the PQ with lowest total cost, rather than greatest
00167   //std::greater<AdjInfo> cmp;
00168   //std::priority_queue<AdjInfo, std::vector<AdjInfo>, std::greater<AdjInfo> > pq(cmp);
00169   std::priority_queue<AdjInfo> pq;
00170 
00171   std::vector<AdjInfo> nodes;
00172   nodes.reserve(alist.size());
00173 
00174   // make list of nodes to keep track of paths and evaluations
00175   for (unsigned i = 0; i < alist.size(); ++i)
00176   {
00177     // Initialize all nodes to infinite cost from the source.
00178     AdjInfo topush;
00179     nodes.push_back(topush);
00180     GNode *node = new GNode;
00181     (*node).id = i + 1;
00182     (*node).evaluated = false;
00183     nodes[i].node = node;
00184     nodes[i].cost = -1;
00185     nodes[i].dInfo.cost = -1;
00186   }
00187 
00188     // Choose a node to be the source or starting point.
00189     // Initialize start node to 0 cost and mark as evaluated.
00190     nodes[start_node - 1].dInfo.cost = 0;
00191     nodes[start_node - 1].node->evaluated = true;
00192     nodes[start_node - 1].dInfo.path.push_back(start_node);
00193 
00194     // For each node, y, adjacent to start node
00195     for (unsigned i = 0; i < alist[start_node - 1].size(); ++i)
00196     {
00197       // save current id to reduce typing...
00198       unsigned y_id = alist[start_node - 1][i].id - 1;
00199       //  1. Relax the node. That is, set y's cost to the cost of all edges from source to y.
00200       //  in this case, the cost to reach the node from source is just the weight of edge
00201       nodes[y_id].dInfo.cost = alist[start_node - 1][i].weight;
00202       //  2. Place y into a priority queue based on its total cost. (Lower is better)
00203       pq.push(nodes[y_id]);
00204       //  3. Add source node as predecessor of y.
00205       nodes[y_id].dInfo.path.push_back(start_node);
00206       nodes[y_id].dInfo.path.push_back(nodes[y_id].node->id);
00207     }
00208 
00209     // While there are nodes in the graph that haven't been evaluated
00210     while (!pq.empty())
00211     {
00212       // Remove a node, x, from the PQ (lowest total cost)
00213       AdjInfo x = pq.top();
00214       pq.pop();
00215       // Mark x as evaluated.
00216       x.node->evaluated = true;
00217       // For each neighbor, y, of x
00218       for (unsigned i = 0; i < alist[x.node->id - 1].size(); ++i)
00219       {
00220         unsigned y_id = alist[x.node->id - 1][i].id - 1;
00221         // Relax y, that is set cost to cost of all edges from source to y
00222         nodes[y_id].cost = nodes[x.node->id - 1].dInfo.cost + alist[x.node->id - 1][i].weight;
00223         // If new cost to reach y is less
00224         if (nodes[y_id].cost < nodes[y_id].dInfo.cost)
00225         {
00226           nodes[y_id].dInfo.cost = nodes[y_id].cost;
00227           // Update list of nodes (path) to y from source.
00228           nodes[y_id].dInfo.path = nodes[x.node->id - 1].dInfo.path;
00229           nodes[y_id].dInfo.path.push_back(nodes[y_id].node->id);
00230           // Place y in the PQ.
00231           pq.push(nodes[y_id]);
00232         }
00233       }
00234     }
00235 
00236   // grab all of the dInfo's from the nodes vector
00237   for (unsigned i = 0; i < nodes.size(); ++i)
00238   {
00239     dInfo.push_back(nodes[i].dInfo);
00240     delete nodes[i].node;
00241   }
00242 
00243   // return the completed dInfo vector
00244   return dInfo;
00245 }
